CITATION: 1971 AIR 720 1971 SCR (3) 469 1971 SCC (1) 458 
ACT:
 Income tax Act. 1922, s. 10(2) (vi), s. 66(1)-Bad debt May relate to money lending business of assessee or other business-Question referred by tribunal to High Court must cover both businesses when the claim can be related to either-Statement of case must contain Tribunal's findings on the facts of the case-Must not be mere resume of facts and arguments.
 Supreme Court Practice-Appeal by special leave against, High Court's judgment in Income-tax Reference-Supreme Court will not interfere with finding of fact given by Tribunal on the evidence recorded in the case.
 
